<p>Hello there!</p>
<p>Today, I want to delve into my custom Org Agenda settings, shedding light on how my workflow compares to the default configurations.</p>
<h2 id="why-customize-org-agenda">Why Customize Org Agenda?</h2>
<p>The default Org Agenda in Emacs is powerful, but with a few tweaks, it can be tailored to fit your personal workflow like a glove. Here&rsquo;s a peek into my settings and why they make a difference.</p>
<h2 id="cleaner-and-clearer-layout">Cleaner and Clearer Layout</h2>
<p>First up, I&rsquo;ve removed tags from the agenda view:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-emacs-lisp" data-lang="emacs-lisp"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">customize-set-variable</span> <span class="ss">&#39;org-agenda-remove-tags</span> <span class="no">t</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>This keeps my agenda clutter-free and focused on the tasks at hand.</p>
<p>I&rsquo;ve also customized the prefix and keyword formats:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-emacs-lisp" data-lang="emacs-lisp"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">customize-set-variable</span> <span class="ss">&#39;org-agenda-prefix-format</span> <span class="s">&#34; %-12c %?-14t% s&#34;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">customize-set-variable</span> <span class="ss">&#39;org-agenda-todo-keyword-format</span> <span class="s">&#34;%-10s&#34;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>This ensures everything is neatly aligned, making it easier to scan through my tasks.</p>
<h2 id="distinct-scheduling-and-deadlines">Distinct Scheduling and Deadlines</h2>
<p>To clearly differentiate between scheduled tasks and deadlines, I&rsquo;ve set up specific leaders:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-emacs-lisp" data-lang="emacs-lisp"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">customize-set-variable</span> <span class="ss">&#39;org-agenda-scheduled-leaders</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">                        <span class="o">&#39;</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&#34;[S] : &#34;</span> <span class="s">&#34;[S] x%3d d.: &#34;</span><span class="p">))</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">customize-set-variable</span> <span class="ss">&#39;org-agenda-deadline-leaders</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">                        <span class="o">&#39;</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&#34;[D] : &#34;</span> <span class="s">&#34;[D] +%3d d.: &#34;</span> <span class="s">&#34;[D] -%3d d.: &#34;</span><span class="p">))</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>This visual cue helps me prioritize my day at a glance.</p>
<h2 id="enhanced-time-management">Enhanced Time Management</h2>
<p>I&rsquo;ve refined the time grid and added a current time string:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-emacs-lisp" data-lang="emacs-lisp"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">customize-set-variable</span> <span class="ss">&#39;org-agenda-time-grid</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">                        <span class="o">&#39;</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="nv">today</span> <span class="nv">require-timed</span> <span class="nv">remove-match</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">                          <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">000</span> <span class="mi">1200</span> <span class="mi">2400</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">                          <span class="s">&#34;:  &#34;</span> <span class="s">&#34;‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà&#34;</span><span class="p">))</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">customize-set-variable</span> <span class="ss">&#39;org-agenda-current-time-string</span> <span class="s">&#34;·êä‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà‚îà now&#34;</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>These adjustments make it easy to keep track of my schedule and current time visually.</p>
<h2 id="custom-commands-for-specific-views">Custom Commands for Specific Views</h2>
<p>I&rsquo;ve added custom commands to cater to different needs:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Weekly Overview</strong>:</li>
